5:
I'm to head into that meeting room
then?
8:
Yes, please! Miguel is already inside
with some of the Guild's most
distinguished merchants.
12:
Bigwigs everywhere, huh... Guess
we'll have to watch our manners.
16:
Here's the parchment detailing
Miguel's request. It's a bit of a
strange one...
20:
"A clever diplomat asks, but never
answers."...Is this the whole message?
22:
Yeah, that's all we got. It's properly
authorized too, since the official seal
of approval's stamped on.
25: Huh... Do you think it's a riddle?
27:
Maybe there's gonna be a quiz? But
we're SUPPOSED to answer those,
right? I don't get it.
29:
I wouldn't put it past him to mess
with us...
31:
But I don't think he'd go through all
this trouble for a prank. Which
means...
34: Listen up, everyone. I've got an idea.
39:
The Academy has agreed to have a
set number of graduates work for
the Guild. We have a number of
positions requiring magical aptitude
to fill—
42:
And they shall choose based on
their personal preferences, yes? I
would have preferred a more
efficient approach, but alas.
45:
They should be given a choice that
allows them to utilize their own
insights.
48:
We'll go with your plans, Miguel. But
be warned the positions chosen will
be carefully screened.
50:
Of course. Only the best will suffice
for a mutually beneficial agreement.
52:
I can only hope the students are
wise enough to see it your way as
well.
55:
By the way, I've heard you've taken a
recent interest in human resources
investment.
57:
Yes, it tickles my fancy as much as
tea.
59:
Then you can tell me... What kind of
business is the young man named
Alk involved in?
62:
He's a simple adventurer who
happens to be intelligent and skilled
at serving tea. You can see why I like
him.
64:
For a mere "adventurer," he knows
an awful lot of powerful people here
in Palpebra—and our neighboring
countries, if you catch my drift.
66:
Yes, he's quite fortunate, isn't he? Ah,
to be a young boy again,
unburdened by grown-ups' political
allegiances. Fortunate, indeed...
69:
...Why are you going out of your way
to protect him? You know we don't
wish him harm.
71:
My reasoning is straightforward: it's
not polite to throw a friend to the
dogs.
73:
I suppose if that's how you view the
matter...
76:
Why not continue to keep the status
quo? It'll be much more profitable to
let him do what he likes.
79:
Very well then. We'll tolerate this
arrangement so long as there are
profits.
83:
Well, well. You must be the orphans
under Miguel's care.
85:
Why do you fret so? And you, young
man, there's no need to be so
nervous.
87:
Please, speak up! We haven't got all
day!
89:
Hahaha, excellent! They pass!
Miguel, you can release them.
93:
Everyone, you now have permission
to talk.
97:
Wow, I can feel my heart pounding...
Can't believe I guessed right...
99:
Why couldn't you have given
instructions like a normal person?
103:
I had every bit of confidence you'd
figure it out. Thank you, everyone.
106:
This another one of your
investments?
109:
An astute observation. You'll be
rewarded a hundred-fold for this
one.
112:
Does this satisfy you, my fellows?
This man and my children have yet
to fall short of my expectations.
113:
They've proved that a capable
person is worth more than a
mountain of gold. Aren't they worth
your investment too?
116:
We'll support your plan. After all,
education is crucial for any youth,
isn't it?
118:
Indeed. Though it may cost time
and money...
119: The payoff is more valuable by far.
